    "faq_items": [
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Is Leadpages good for beginners with no coding experience?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Absolutely. Leadpages is designed for ease of use. Its drag-and-drop editor and goal-oriented templates mean you can create a professional, high-converting landing page without writing a single line of code. The interface is intuitive, and helpful tooltips guide you.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Can I use my own domain name with Leadpages?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Yes, you can. While you get a free leadpages.com subdomain, connecting your custom domain (e.g., yourbrand.com/offers) is a standard feature. This builds brand trust and makes your URLs cleaner and more professional.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How does the A/B testing in Leadpages work?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "It’s seamless. After creating your first page (A), you can duplicate it to create a variant (B) and change one element like the headline or button color. Leadpages then automatically splits your traffic between them and declares a winner based on which version converts better, giving you clear data for optimization.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What kind of integrations does Leadpages support?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Leadpages has a vast library of integrations. It connects smoothly with major email marketing platforms (like Mailchimp, AWeber, ConvertKit), CRMs, webinar services, payment processors like Stripe, and productivity tools. The setup is typically just a few clicks.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
